{{zh-forms|ss=⿰亻⿻乚二}}

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}}: a short&#x2010;tailed bird (e.g. a sparrow). In addition to referring to {{och-l|隹|short-tailed bird}}, it also is the original form of {{och-l|鷕|cry of a bird}} with the intermediate form {{och-l|*唯}}.<ref>布之道『[http://www.kaom.net/sgy_bzd.php 廣韻形聲考]』</ref>

Compare {{zh-l|*鳥}}.

===Etymology===
Perhaps from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*twil}}; compare {{cog|bo|མཆིལ་པ|t=a little bird}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Cognate with {{och-l|鵻|id=2}} "a kind of bird (turtle-dove?)" > {{och-l|騅}} "horse of that bird's color > horse of mixed grey and white color".

